fetch(url + "?" + params).then((rsp) => {
rsp.text().then((responseText) => {
message.innerHTML = responseText;
});
});
```
A diagnostic URL is fetched with a query parameter (`\u57f7\u4e8b`) and the response body injected into the DOM. If the server reflects the request parameter in its response (which URICheckEncodingMonitor does by design — it echoes whether encoding works), this is a **reflected XSS** if the echo is not properly escaped.
